title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta 1934, WWII, Brescia Blank Slide, G prefix
location: Fort Thomas, KY near Cincinnati, Northern Kentucky, Kentucky
postcontent: If you can read this, it is still available--I will deactivate ASAP if sold or traded.  I will ship and have an 03 FFL (C&R).  This is one of the rarer variations of a Beretta 1934, .380 ACP or 9 mm Corto (Italian for "short"), made in later 1943 for the Italian Army.  Original Beretta magazine.  As I understand it, when Mussolini's Fascist government was deposed, for a short time the Italian Army kept fighting and the Beretta plants, both in Gardone & Brescia kept making pistols.  Not knowing what was going to shake out politically, Beretta left the slides blank. The earlier versions had dates and other legends, but between governments, until the Nazi's took total control and started overseeing the plants, this is what was produced.  There's a small Brescia proof on the left tang and BM in a box at the butt next to the lanyard loop.  All matching numbers, in condition as you see it.  Bore has some minor frosting but good rifling.  I have shot it and it worked well, no known mechanical issues.  The impression I get is this was carried, used, and surrendered later in the war.  No import marks, most likely a GI bring back.  It's a duplicate, so wife says something has to go.
